1
00:00:13,180 --> 00:01:42,352
♪

2
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:50,277
♪

3
00:01:50,277 --> 00:01:51,820
Are all of them‐‐

4
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:55,490
Should you see fit,
they are yours to command.

5
00:01:55,490 --> 00:02:00,203
♪

6
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:03,206
You have said that your wings
have the strength to carry

7
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:06,126
our dreams to the
heavens themselves.

8
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,795
I believe in those
words of yours.

9
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:12,257
Now I ask that you
lend us those wings,

10
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:16,219
and pave the road to a new era.

11
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:18,347
A new era

12
00:02:18,347 --> 00:02:20,390
of Genesis.

13
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,392
You are our Sky King.

14
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:25,103
(rumbling)

15
00:02:25,103 --> 00:03:07,145
♪

16
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:10,524
(bells ringing)

17
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:18,031
♪

18
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,325
Your wish is my
command, my lord.

19
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,828
Ask and you shall receive.

20
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:25,497
You'll really do anything,
no matter what?

21
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:27,541
Yes, anything, you have my word.

22
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:29,543
I see.

23
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:32,546
Then get me an espresso
and dozen chocolate donuts.

24
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:35,298
(chuckling)

25
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:37,968
You said anything, right?

26
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:44,641
All of a sudden I've got a team
of 350 riders to order around.

27
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,893
That's wack.

28
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:50,564
(footsteps approaching)

29
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:51,857
What's up, Ume?

30
00:03:51,857 --> 00:03:55,861
Ikki, are you sure you wanna
be the leader of Genesis?

31
00:03:55,861 --> 00:03:58,697
Well, I don't know
for sure yet, but‐‐

32
00:03:58,697 --> 00:04:00,532
Do you have any
idea what it means

33
00:04:00,532 --> 00:04:03,952
to take on a job like that?

34
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:05,996
Did anyone even
tell you why Genesis

35
00:04:05,996 --> 00:04:07,706
was formed in the first place?

36
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:09,791
Do you know what
their objective is?

37
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:14,045
Hm, they're gonna tear down
the Tower of Trophaeum, right?

38
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:17,048
‐Ume, stop.
‐But someone has to tell him!

39
00:04:17,048 --> 00:04:19,217
I know how you feel, but
no matter what you say,

40
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:21,887
you can't get through
to a bird brain like him.

41
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:24,431
But I, I still like Ikki!

42
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:26,224
I don't want us
to have to fight.

43
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:28,643
I mean, Ikki's like part
of the family, I want him

44
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:31,062
to stay with us
forever, don't you?

45
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:33,815
Whoa, wait, hold on a sec.

46
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:35,901
Why did you say we're
gonna have to fight, huh?

47
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:38,236
You need to stop
taking orders from Simca,

48
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:42,365
especially when you don't even
know what you're agreeing to.

49
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,201
I don't get it,
why do you all have

50
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:46,745
a bug up your ass about Genesis?

51
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:49,247
♪

52
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:52,334
I'm sorry, Ikki, but
we can't talk about that.

53
00:04:52,334 --> 00:05:31,331
♪

54
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:34,251
Okay everyone, here are
the handouts to fill you in

55
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:37,587
about this year's class trip.

56
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,799
(bells ringing)

57
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:44,594
(indistinct conversations)

58
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:50,725
I guess I'd better
take him one too.

59
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,478
♪

60
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:56,106
Hey, Crow, what you
gonna do about Genesis?

61
00:05:56,106 --> 00:05:58,650
If you go along with this, then
we'll have the strongest team

62
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:00,485
in all of Japan
under our control.

63
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:03,405
‐Would that be awesome or what?
‐Yeah, but don't you think

64
00:06:03,405 --> 00:06:06,157
this whole thing is
too good to be true?

65
00:06:06,157 --> 00:06:10,078
Do you even realize that you
have to be at least B class

66
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:12,080
before you even think
about challenging

67
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,374
the summon of the
Tower of Trophaeum.

68
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:16,835
Since we're still E Class
that means we have to win

69
00:06:16,835 --> 00:06:19,754
nine battles in
a row to advance.

70
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:21,506
Nine wins in a row?

71
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:24,634
Not only that, but our
team possesses Regalia.

72
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:25,844
So we need to understand

73
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:28,763
just what kinda
danger we're up against.

74
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:31,600
‐So what do you think, Ikki?
‐It's obvious, isn't it?

75
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,852
We kill every team
that gets in our way.

76
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:36,563
Come on, what don't
you cut the crap, Crow?

77
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:39,274
I mean, you're pretty good,
but me and Akito aside,

78
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:40,942
you guys are still beginners.

79
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:43,111
Yeah, well maybe it would
be a good idea to see

80
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:44,946
how Akito feels about this too.

81
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:48,658
That's how you roll, Kazu.

82
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:50,952
Wow, they're letting
you out already?

83
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:53,705
Well, I still have to
take it easy for a while,

84
00:06:53,705 --> 00:06:56,041
but they said I can
go home at least.

85
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:59,002
(water flowing)

86
00:07:01,046 --> 00:07:04,674
Akito said he doesn't really
care what you guys do.

87
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,384
He did?

88
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:08,053
He can't ride with
the rest of the team

89
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:10,305
until our injuries
heal, so he says

90
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,724
if Ikki's serious about
taking over Genesis,

91
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:15,644
then there's no reason
not to go for it.

92
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:18,229
Well, you haven't convinced me.

93
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:20,982
Hmph!

94
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:23,234
‐Aw, come on, Buccha!
‐Let him go.

95
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:26,529
Oh yeah.

96
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:30,033
Is that a Kyoto tour guide?

97
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:33,662
Yeah, we're going
on a field trip.

98
00:07:33,662 --> 00:07:35,747
What, is there something wrong?

99
00:07:35,747 --> 00:07:38,958
Well, that sounds like fun
and all, but you can't go

100
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,044
unless you have money
saved up, right?

101
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:43,254
Money, oh, yeah right.

102
00:07:43,254 --> 00:07:45,924
I guess you kinda just
ran away from home, huh?

103
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:49,928
I'll talk to Tom‐Tom tomorrow
and see what she can do.

104
00:07:49,928 --> 00:07:51,930
Okay.

105
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:54,891
(dog barking)

106
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:07,779
(wind blowing)

107
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:25,088
♪

108
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:28,675
What up?

109
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:29,968
I wanted to ask you something.

110
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,928
Did all these teams
aim for the Trophaeum?

111
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:33,847
Most of them, by the way,

112
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:37,308
I heard your team was going
to take control over Genesis.

113
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:38,893
We haven't decided yet.

114
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:42,480
Really we don't even know
how this whole thing works.

115
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,232
At this point,
we couldn't challenge

116
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:46,109
the Trophaeum if we wanted to.

117
00:08:46,109 --> 00:08:47,527
I mean, how are
we supposed to know

118
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,696
what the teams on
the top are like?

119
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:52,991
You'll know, actually
you've known for long time.

120
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:55,827
Say what, what's that
supposed to mean?

121
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:57,829
It means exactly what I said.

122
00:08:57,829 --> 00:08:59,914
Remember first night
you came here?

123
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:03,126
Which team's emblem were
you wearing on your jacket?

124
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:04,627
Wait.

125
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:07,589
You mean, Sleeping Forest?

126
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:32,155
♪

127
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:36,534
So, Ringo's team is
at the top of the tower?

128
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,495
Now you're finally
starting to get it.

129
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:41,664
Ringo Noyamano is successor
to Sleeping Forest.

130
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:46,044
You see, after the Kilik
incident, their team fell apart.

131
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:50,256
Now as far as most riders know,
they're nothing but a legend.

132
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:53,718
But ones at the top
know the truth.

133
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:55,345
Kilik?

134
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:57,722
It happened before
Ringo was on the team.

135
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:02,268
Someone betrayed others
and took out the boss.

136
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,605
That must've been the guy
Rika was talking about.

137
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,066
That means Genesis is‐‐

138
00:10:08,066 --> 00:10:10,318
It's a megastorm
created to bring down

139
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,653
the Tower of Trophaeum

140
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:14,989
and crush Ringo Noyamano's
Sleeping Forest.

141
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,118
Now, do you understand?

142
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:21,496
This is really starting to
get fun now, don't you think?

143
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:23,873
I don't see what's
so fun about it.

144
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:28,086
Well, maybe not for you I guess.

145
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:29,921
So what're you gonna do?

146
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:32,465
Are you gonna slap me
like you did last time?

147
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:35,426
I told you, Ikki
is not your toy.

148
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:38,179
I never said he was, did I?

149
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:40,890
He's much more
important than that,

150
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,476
'cause I believe that Little
Crow is the one whose wings

151
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,437
will carry me higher
than I've ever flown before.

152
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:50,108
Mm‐mm, you're wrong.

153
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:52,235
But he said he'd
accept, didn't he?

154
00:10:52,235 --> 00:10:56,447
That's why you're so mad, right?

155
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:59,450
You can't stand to lose
your little toy, can you?

156
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,703
I'm sorry, but he's free now.

157
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,538
It's all up to him.

158
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:06,249
Just sit back and
enjoy the show.

159
00:11:06,249 --> 00:11:07,959
See you around!

160
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:19,762
♪

161
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,556
Hey, Aeon, got my donuts?

162
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,933
No, but I heard
you're going to Kyoto.

163
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:27,395
‐Yeah, it's for our class trip.
‐Perfect timing.

164
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:30,231
Now that you've been elected
the new leader of Genesis,

165
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,901
there's a king in Kyoto
I'd like you to meet.

166
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:36,654
‐I trust you don't mind.
‐If it's okay with you,

167
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:39,157
could we talk about this
leader stuff some other time?

168
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:42,285
I've kinda got a lot of things
on my mind and my head hurts.

169
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:43,661
Sure, that's fine.

170
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:46,331
Whenever you feel up to
it just give me a call.

171
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:48,917
Yeah, later!

172
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:54,297
(whooshing noise)

173
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:57,050
Hey, Ringo.

174
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:07,268
I see, you're not supposed
to be able to go on the trip

175
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:09,187
if you don't have the money.

176
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:11,356
I'm sorry, Akito, but
it looks like you might

177
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:13,399
have to stay behind
and have study hall.

178
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:16,236
Come on, there's gotta
be something you can do.

179
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:17,987
I'm sure as a teacher
you make enough money

180
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,448
‐to pay for him, right?
‐What?

181
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:24,035
Well, why don't you
just ask Mr. Orihara?

182
00:12:24,035 --> 00:12:26,579
(clearing throat)

183
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:29,290
Well, you know, I'd love
to help you guys out,

184
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:33,586
but I just spent all my savings
on a new punching bag, so...

185
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:38,216
♪

186
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:41,386
I'm sorry about this, it's not
that I don't have any money.

187
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,596
I actually saved up plenty
when I used to work

188
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,056
for the Marufu G‐Men.

189
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,517
Then what the hell
is the problem?

190
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:49,644
Well, it's not a matter
of having money,

191
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:52,063
it's a matter of getting to it.

192
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:58,152
♪

193
00:12:58,152 --> 00:12:59,821
Ringo!

194
00:12:59,821 --> 00:13:02,782
♪

195
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:04,409
Gonna have a
Kogarasumaru meeting

196
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,160
at our hideout after class.

197
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,121
But Ikki, I‐‐

198
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,165
I want you to be there too.

199
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:13,209
All right?

200
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:24,012
♪

201
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:33,354
♪

202
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:36,316
(birds chirping)

203
00:13:39,277 --> 00:13:42,780
I found it.

204
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:45,950
So you sure that's where
your bankbook's at, Akito?

205
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,411
(beeping)

206
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,121
That's it, I'm positive.

207
00:13:50,121 --> 00:13:53,416
My brother and I lived in
that trailer all our lives.

208
00:13:53,416 --> 00:14:01,257
♪

209
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:04,552
Great, we're totally screwed.

210
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:06,971
I don't know about you,
but I'd rather stay home

211
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,057
than risk getting shot at.

212
00:14:09,057 --> 00:14:12,977
♪

213
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:15,688
Well, not me, I never
got to go on field trips

214
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:18,024
when I was in grade school.

215
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:19,901
I didn't want Rika
to have to pay,

216
00:14:19,901 --> 00:14:22,028
so every year I stayed at home.

217
00:14:22,028 --> 00:14:24,572
♪

218
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,616
Of course I was
really frustrated,

219
00:14:26,616 --> 00:14:29,994
but it wasn't because I
wanted to go on a field trip.

220
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:33,498
In fact, it didn't really hit
me until the class came back.

221
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:35,458
When I saw everyone
laughing and talking,

222
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:38,586
then I realized that they
were all sharing memories

223
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,797
that I could never be a part of.

224
00:14:40,797 --> 00:14:43,841
♪

225
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:45,510
I've made my decision,
all right?

226
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:48,387
Kogarasumaru,
prepare to move out.

227
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:50,848
♪

228
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:54,060
‐Ikki.
‐You can't be serious.

229
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:57,105
I mean, what're we
gonna do about Akito?

230
00:14:57,105 --> 00:15:00,066
Even if we could sneak into
the trailer we'd still need him

231
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:03,694
to show us where
the bankbook is.

232
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:07,698
Don't worry, even if Akito can't
ride, he's still coming with us.

233
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:10,368
Whether we're going to Kyoto
or the top of the Trophaeum,

234
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,328
we do everything as a team.

235
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:14,705
This isn't just about
some class trip.

236
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:16,290
It's about our dream.

237
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:19,710
This time I want all of us
to share our memories,

238
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:23,047
because now we're on
our way to the top,

239
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:26,384
and we have to believe that
what we're doing is right.

240
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:29,053
We have to believe, 'cause
we'll be crushing the dreams

241
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:31,055
of all the other riders
on the way to the top,

242
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:33,558
‐and that's fine by me!
‐Ikki.

243
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:37,061
Right now we have control over
all the riders in Genesis,

244
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:40,064
but in one month, I say,

245
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:44,402
we declare war and show them
what we're really made of!

246
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:46,362
If we can bring them
down with our own power,

247
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:48,114
then they'll know we're serious.

248
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:49,991
If we're gonna rule them,
we're gonna make them

249
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:52,493
bow down ourselves.

250
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:55,204
I think you landed on your
head one too many times.

251
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:58,207
However...

252
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:04,088
Count on me to fill
in as Akito's leg.

253
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:07,258
Now, come on, let's go
get the savings passbook!

254
00:16:07,258 --> 00:16:11,137
Oh, by the way, it just
so happens that Aeon said

255
00:16:11,137 --> 00:16:15,099
we're supposed to meet
a new king in Kyoto.

256
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:17,768
That means this is our big
chance to conquer Kyoto,

257
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:20,938
but before that, we gotta
get back Akito's bankbook!

258
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:23,566
We'll call it
Operation City Hunter

259
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:26,777
Wriggling in the
Darkness, let's go!

260
00:16:26,777 --> 00:16:29,864
What kind of stupid ass name
for an operation is that?

261
00:16:29,864 --> 00:16:32,283
Stop complaining, go!

262
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:34,452
Kogarasumaru!

263
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:36,746
(together)
Kill 'em dead!

264
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:51,761
♪

265
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:54,096
I'm sorry, sir,
this road is closed.

266
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:56,307
If you wait, we'll
be done in a minute.

267
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:58,476
All right, but hurry up,
if you take too long

268
00:16:58,476 --> 00:17:00,811
I'll put a cap in your ass.

269
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,188
Good thing our boss is stupid,

270
00:17:02,188 --> 00:17:04,607
and doesn't lock up
the equipment at night.

271
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:07,777
Yeah, guess we're lucky
we work for a stupid boss.

272
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:14,992
♪

273
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:16,452
Open up!

274
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:19,413
(growling)

275
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:21,582
♪

276
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:25,086
So, uh, where'd you get
this sweet looking ride?

277
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:28,005
Hands off, jerkwad,
hey, don't I know you?

278
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:31,342
What, who, me, no.

279
00:17:31,342 --> 00:17:32,677
All right, just like we planned.

280
00:17:32,677 --> 00:17:34,804
You've got 30 seconds
to find that book.

281
00:17:34,804 --> 00:17:36,389
Right.

282
00:17:36,389 --> 00:17:48,859
♪

283
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:50,403
I imagined this
place looking like

284
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:53,656
a torture chamber or something.

285
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:55,866
But actually,

286
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:58,119
now that I'm here,

287
00:17:58,119 --> 00:18:00,538
it kinda reminds me of my place.

288
00:18:00,538 --> 00:18:05,042
♪

289
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:06,961
‐That bastard!
‐This isn't right.

290
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:10,006
I'm sure I left it in here,
I know I didn't take it out.

291
00:18:10,006 --> 00:18:12,967
Kaito must have moved it,
I don't understand.

292
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:14,760
Why would he have taken it?

293
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,597
I'm sick of this, I'll
take a back street.

294
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:20,349
No, just wait a little longer!

295
00:18:20,349 --> 00:18:22,643
Crap, what the hell
are those idiots doing?

296
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:25,521
‐Ahhhh!
‐That's not good!

297
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:27,607
Well, that's gonna
suck for Ikki.

298
00:18:27,607 --> 00:18:29,734
I think I'll go home and pack.

299
00:18:29,734 --> 00:18:33,571
(engine whirring)

300
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:36,574
Well, this sucks.

301
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:39,452
So have you found it yet, Akito?

302
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:42,079
I can't figure out where
he could've moved it.

303
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:45,499
What're we gonna do now?

304
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:48,377
Don't move, ya filthy
little thief.

305
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:51,339
I gotta tell you, you picked
the wrong car to rob.

306
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:53,716
(shouting)

307
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:55,926
(thudding)

308
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,678
Akira!

309
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:02,141
What in the hell
are you doing here?

310
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:04,268
What, what am I‐‐how about you?

311
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:08,189
If Kaito finds out you're here,
you two are gonna be road kill.

312
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:13,569
(whooshing noise)

313
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:19,200
Kaito, wait, who's driving?

314
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,869
‐You are.
‐Ahh!

315
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:25,206
(tires skidding)

316
00:19:25,206 --> 00:19:28,834
(grumbling)

317
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:30,961
‐Big brother.
‐Looks like I must have had

318
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:33,464
a little too much
to drink last night.

319
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:35,841
I'm having some kind
of weird hallucination.

320
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,969
That must be it,
no other explanation,

321
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,305
'cause I remember kicking
Akito out of the unit

322
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:44,308
when Akira came back.

323
00:19:44,308 --> 00:19:46,310
Kicking me out?

324
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,771
And there's no way that
piece of shit traitor

325
00:19:48,771 --> 00:19:50,815
would've had the
nerve to come back,

326
00:19:50,815 --> 00:19:53,484
especially not with
a damn crow with him,

327
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:57,738
'cause he knows if he did
come back, I'd kick his ass.

328
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:59,573
Actually, that reminds me,

329
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:02,618
that useless little brat
left his bankbook behind.

330
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:04,620
I think I put it in
that bag under my bed

331
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:05,830
with the rest of his crap.

332
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:09,041
I don't need it, so I guess
I might as well throw it away.

333
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,877
Now I'm sure when I open
my eyes and turn around,

334
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:13,921
that hallucination will be gone,

335
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:15,923
if it knows what's good for it.

336
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:19,552
♪

337
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:21,470
Thank you, Kaito.

338
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:29,270
♪

339
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:32,231
Wow, you can actually be nice,
I'm pretty impressed.

340
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,359
You're too naive, Akira,
you should know better.

341
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:37,153
It's all part of the plan.

342
00:20:37,153 --> 00:20:41,741
Now that Akito's a part of
Genesis, we have an inside man.

343
00:20:41,741 --> 00:20:48,456
♪

344
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:52,042
(engine whirring)

345
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:55,045
♪

346
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:58,090
Guess you guys are still
brothers after all, huh?

347
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,718
‐I'm glad everything worked out.
‐Yeah, me too.

348
00:21:00,718 --> 00:21:04,013
I was afraid I wouldn't get to
go on vacation with everyone.

349
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:07,224
♪

350
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:10,603
The king of Kyoto is one of the
three leaders of Team Trident.

351
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:12,897
They're the most powerful
team in the Kansai region

352
00:21:12,897 --> 00:21:16,484
with over 200 riders under them.

353
00:21:16,484 --> 00:21:19,820
This could get ugly, looks like
they'll definitely need my‐‐

354
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:22,239
I mean, Akito's help.

355
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:24,241
Hey, something wrong, Akito?

356
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,869
Huh, oh, nothing.

357
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,839
You know, Ume's been
crying for a long time.

358
00:21:42,927 --> 00:21:45,095
You should probably talk
to her when we get back.

359
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:47,556
Way ahead of you.

360
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:51,435
(whooshing noise)

361
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:53,270
(train buzzing)

362
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:56,899
I hope you're ready, Kyoto,
'cause here we come!

363
00:21:56,899 --> 00:23:42,379
♪

364
00:23:46,383 --> 00:23:48,761
Nijo Castle and
Kiyomizu Temple, huh?

365
00:23:48,761 --> 00:23:50,554
Japan has such a rich heritage.

366
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:52,473
Why are you talking
like a tourist?

367
00:23:52,473 --> 00:23:53,891
Don't you know that class trips

368
00:23:53,891 --> 00:23:55,726
are the perfect
romantic getaway?

369
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:58,145
Well, that's what I was hoping
until that weird girl showed up.

370
00:23:58,145 --> 00:24:00,189
‐Who is she anyway?
‐I don't know.

371
00:24:00,189 --> 00:24:03,233
‐I think she's a fan of me.
‐You have to keep your guard up.

372
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:05,194
You never know when
someone might attack.

373
00:24:05,194 --> 00:24:07,112
Got it, next time on Air Gear:

374
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:11,742
Genesis, Kansai Branch, here
come Benkei and Yoshitsune!

375
00:24:11,742 --> 00:24:14,662
♪

